 675:Drivers/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c **** /**
 676:Drivers/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****   * @brief  Selects the specified I2C NACK position in master receiver mode.
 677:Drivers/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****   *         This function is useful in I2C Master Receiver mode when the number
 678:Drivers/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****   *         of data to be received is equal to 2. In this case, this function 
 679:Drivers/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****   *         should be called (with parameter I2C_NACKPosition_Next) before data 
 680:Drivers/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****   *         reception starts,as described in the 2-byte reception procedure 
 681:Drivers/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****   *         recommended in Reference Manual in Section: Master receiver.                
 682:Drivers/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****   * @param  I2Cx: where x can be 1 or 2 to select the I2C peripheral.
 683:Drivers/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****   * @param  I2C_NACKPosition: specifies the NACK position. 
 684:Drivers/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****   *   This parameter can be one of the following values:
 685:Drivers/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****   *     @arg I2C_NACKPosition_Next: indicates that the next byte will be the last
 686:Drivers/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****   *          received byte.  
 687:Drivers/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****   *     @arg I2C_NACKPosition_Current: indicates that current byte is the last 
 688:Drivers/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****   *          received byte.
 689:Drivers/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****   *            
 690:Drivers/STM32F10x_StdPeriph_Driver/src/stm32f10x_i2c.c ****   * @note    This function configures the same bit (POS) as I2C_PECPositionConfig() 
